`configurations.runtimeClasspath` is a generated [Gradle Kotlin DSL accessor](https://docs.gradle.org/7.6/userguide/kotlin_dsl.html#type-safe-accessors), and these are only available inside `*.gradle.kts` files. 

Instead you&#39;ll have to access the configuration by the name, using [`ConfigurationContainer.getByName()`](https://docs.gradle.org/7.6/javadoc/org/gradle/api/artifacts/ConfigurationContainer.html#getByName-java.lang.String-).

Conveniently, [`JavaPlugin`](https://docs.gradle.org/7.6urrent/javadoc/org/gradle/api/plugins/JavaPlugin.html) provides the name of the `runtimeClasspath` Configuration, so it can be imported and used directly (rather than using a &#39;magic&#39; string).

```kotlin
// import JavaPlugin
import org.gradle.api.plugins.JavaPlugin

// (existing imports)
// import ...

fun Project.makeExecutableJar (name: String, main: String?, sset: SourceSet) : TaskProvider&lt;Jar&gt; {
    // access the runtimeClasspath configuration
    val runtimeClasspathConfiguration = configurations.named(JavaPlugin.RUNTIME_CLASSPATH_CONFIGURATION_NAME)
    
    return tasks.register&lt;Jar&gt;(name) {
        dependsOn(runtimeClasspathConfiguration )
        // ...
    }
}
```

